article.headline: Gonzaga 76, San Francisco 46
article.story: SPOKANE, Wash. -- Austin Daye scored a career high 25 points as Gonzaga beat San Francisco 85-51 on Saturday night to remain undefeated in the West Coast Conference. Micah Downs added 15 for Gonzaga (12-4, 3-0), which won its fourth straight game and has blown out all three of its WCC rivals so far. They beat Santa Clara by 42 points on Thursday, as Daye scored 20. Daye made 10-of-14 shots, and added nine rebounds. His previous high was 22 points against Arizona this season. Dior Lowhorn led San Francisco (8-11, 0-4) with 15, five below his WCC-leading average. The Dons have lost seven of their past eight games, and four in a row.
